HEADWORD: Ectolecithal
<hw>Ec`to*lec"i*thal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ecto-</ets> + Gr. <?/ the yolk of an egg.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having the food yolk, at the commencement of
segmentation, in a peripheral position, and the cleavage process
confined to the center of the egg; <as>as, <ex>ectolecithal</ex>
ova</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ectomere</ent>⟦br⟧
